---
globs: *.ts,*.js
alwaysApply: false
---

When creating a javascript/typescript script that will be run as a command line tool, add this to the main function calls.
Also keep await not prevent .then & .catch if possible.

```typescript
if (import.meta.main) {
	try {
		await main();
	} catch (error) {
		console.error(error);
		process.exit(1);
	}
}
```

After editing a file, run linting and formatting commands. Usually: "npm run lint" and "npm run format:check"
